defaultMain Submissiondefault&#xa0;
default1.  How best to protect minors from accessing adult contentdefaultFiltersdefaultThe vast majority of experts and childcare experts, including major children’s charities, agree that ISP level filters with a default of porn off, and an ‘opt-in’ for over 18s who wish to access all content, are currently the best way to protect minors.  What was announced by the 
defaultPrimer
default Minister in July was slightly different (all customers will be presented with an unavoidable choice to apply filters or not) but we applaud his work to have this introduced for all customers of the big 6 ISPs by the end of 2014.  However all ISPs should be included as soon as possible, and the system will only work properly if there is strict age verification.  Close monitoring is vital.  
defaultOfcom
default, given this task by the Prime Minister, must without 
defaultdelay develop
default clear standards, with which all ISPs should be required to comply.  Ongoing monitoring will also be 
defaultkey
default.
defaultRecent research from the magazine PC Pro (Sept 2013) shows that 80% of parental controls fail to filter explicit material, with only 3 out of 5 of the most popular website filters being 100% effective in blocking pornography.   This is an egregious situation for parents and carers and demonstrates clearly the need for automatic ISP level filters.
defaultISP level filters should apply to all internet-enabled devices including:
defaulti
default) 
defaultmobile
default phones.   All 3G networks offer content filtering and it works well enough.  However 
defaultVoda
default, EE and O2 all let VPNs and proxy servers through, so if you know how, you can bypass the filters.
defaultVodaphone
default and EE (tested by our technical adviser) do not enable Google safe search and so a simple search for obvious keywords and clicking on images yields lots of images. But usually if you click on one to go to the website, the content blocker will block it.   This is something Google really needs to do more work on
defaultFigures suggest 91% of pre-teens and teens 
defaultwho
default have a 
defaultsmartphone
default have internet access 24/7.    The pornography industry’s main target is the 12-17 age group and they are putting huge efforts into monetising the mobile phone.   Between 22 and 25   September the pornography industry 
defaultXBiz
default conference was held at the Radisson Hotel in Bloomsbury in London and their focus
default defaultwas on opposingdefault&#xa0;defaultUKdefault&#xa0;defaultplans to limit access to online pornography in thedefault&#xa0;defaultUKdefault  
