defaultWifi
default.  Free public 
defaultWifi
default is used by many young people as it saves their own allocated usage and they can access content without their parents’ knowledge if they wish.  It was supposed 
defaultto  have
default been filtered by the end of August, but research this week shows that more 
defaultthan half of free public Wi-Fi networks let users access porn, violence and drugs. Mobile security firm 
defaultAdaptiveMobile
default, tested the web filters on public networks across the country and discovered one in three UK cafes and restaurants have no filtering in place at all - leaving children in danger of accessing pornography.   
defaultThe Government will clearly have to work much more closely with the industry and all who offer public 
defaultWifi
default to ensure progress is made in line with the Prime Minister’s timetable.
defaultEducation defaultParents are the most important people to reach with education about computers: they need to learn how to set up safety measures; to have an understanding of what children can and are doing online; to know how best to communicate with their children about internet use, and measures to protect their children.  They must also be encouraged to talk a great deal more to their children about these issues and be helped with the skills needed
default.
defaultHere also the Prime Minister has promised to make much more use of government resources to raise awareness among parents and empower them, and we welcome that.
defaultChildren need education too, but it must be remembered that teens’ neural chemistry and reward signals means they are inclined towards risk taking and impulsive behaviour.   Their natural curiosity and desire for independence can make them forget education and warnings by parents and other adults.
defaultSchooldefault&#xa0;
defaultResearch showing serious harm from pornographydefaultFinally it is very important to remember exactly why we need to protect children from adult content.  The following examples give an idea of the large body of compelling international evidence showing serious damage to sexual development and behaviour from pornography:
defaultA.  The Sexual Trauma and Psychological Programme, University of Pennsylvania:
default&#xa0;
default‘
defaultOverall the body of research on pornography reveals … it functions as a teacher, permission–giver, and a trigger of … negative behaviours and attitudes.
default&#xa0;
default The damage is seen in men, women and children, and to both married and single adults ... pathological behaviours, illegal behaviours and some behaviours that are both illegal and pathological.’
default&#xa0;
defaultThis research forms part of ‘The Social Costs of Pornography: A Statement of Findings and Recommendations,’ the findings of an inquiry and consultation that ran from 2010 – 2012, sponsored by the Witherspoon Institute and the Institute for the Psychological Sciences.  Fifty four of the ablest professionals and academics in law, medicine, political theory, philosophy, religious studies, history and several other disciplines contributed.
default&#xa0;
defaultB.  "
defaultA meta-analysis of the published research on the effects of pornography," Elizabeth 
defaultOddone-Paolucci
default, Mark 
defaultGenuis
default and Claudio 
defaultViolato
default, University of Calgary. 
defaultMedicine, Mind and Adolescence, 1997.
default The 46 studies (from 1965 to 1995) included 12,323 people. "
defaultThe results are clear and consistent; exposure to pornographic material puts one at an increased risk for developing sexually deviant tendencies, committing sexual offences, experiencing difficulties in one's intimate relationships, and accepting the rape myth. In order to promote a healthy and stable society, it is time that we attend to the culmination of sound empirical research.  The rise in sexual crimes, sexual dysfunction and family breakdown may be linked to increased availability and use of porn."
default&#xa0;
defaultMay we point out that these are both extremely extensive pieces of work
default, the former being a multifaceted, multidisciplinary and scholarly exploration of the issue, and the latter a meta-analysis of previous research.
default&#xa0;
defaultC.  Brain scan images of porn addicts show that watching online 'adult' sites can alter our grey matter, which may lead to a change in sexual tastes.   
defaultNew research by Cambridge University 
defaultneuropsychiatrist
default Dr
default&#xa0;
defaultValerie 
defaultVoon
default 
defaultshows that men who say they are addicted to porn … develop changes in the same area as heroin addicts – the reward centre – that changes in drug addicts.  (Norman 
defaultDoidge
default, 
defaultThe
default Guardian 26 Sept 2013)
default&#xa0;
defaultD.  That so many children and young people are already manifesting serious effects from their easy access to pornography and other harmful content is reason enough for Government action to take on a sense of urgency (London Portman Clinic is one source).
